<h1>Component-Based Software Engineering</h1>

<h2>Definition of a Software Component</h2>

<h2>A software component is a <font color=red>software element</font> that conforms to a
<font color=red>component model</font> and can be independently deployed and
composed without modification according to a <font color=red>composition standard</font>.
</h2>

<h2>A software element is a sequence of program statements to
perform certain computation by the computer.</h2>
